title: So You Think You Can Dance Canada Season 4
description:
"So You Think You Can Dance Canada" was a dance reality show and competition that aired on the CTV television network for four seasons. It was hosted by MuchMusic VJ and ETalk correspondent Leah Miller.

The series was based on the original American TV series "So You Think You Can Dance". Auditions for the first season began April 7, 2008 in Vancouver, British Columbia and ended in Toronto, Ontario on June 8, 2008. The show premiered on September 11, 2008 beginning with the Toronto auditions.

There were 23 episodes broadcast in season 4, with the first on June 20, 2011, and the final one on September 11, 2011. Two days after the fourth season finale, CTV announced that it was not renewing "So You Think You Can Dance Canada". In its announcement, the network noted that Season 4 was the lowest rated one to date, having lost 31% of its viewership since its initial season. However, it is difficult to compare ratings across seasons, as the first three installments aired in the fall, while the fourth aired in the summer - which traditionally has lower viewership across the board.

Season 4 still garnered over one million viewers and was the network's number 2 Canadian entertainment series - and number 1 in the 18-34 demographic
